            <h2>The Power of Ecosystem Integration</h2>
            <p>
                Phase 4 brings WIA-CORE-002 into the broader context of digital infrastructure and the WIA
                standard family. While the previous phases established standalone consent management capabilities,
                Phase 4 focuses on integrationвҖ”connecting consent to user intentions, API access control, social
                platforms, and third-party tools to create a seamless, user-centric privacy ecosystem.
            </p>
            <h2>The WIA Family Connection</h2>
            <p>
                WIA-CORE-002 is part of the WIA (World Internet Association) family of standards, each addressing
                a critical aspect of digital infrastructure. Understanding how these standards work together
                amplifies the value of each individual standard.
            </p>
            <h3>Integration with WIA-INTENT</h3>
            <p>
                WIA-INTENT captures user intentions and preferences. When combined with WIA-CORE-002, user
                consent becomes an expression of intent:
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">{
  "intentId": "intent-abc123",
  "userId": "user-789012",
  "type": "privacy-preference",
  "expression": {
    "consentPreferences": {
      "marketing": "opt-out",
      "analytics": "opt-in-anonymous",
      "personalization": "opt-in-full"
    },
    "dataRetention": "minimal",
    "thirdPartySharing": "prohibited"
  },
  "appliesTo": ["all-services"],
  "wiaCore002ConsentId": "consent-550e8400..."
}</div>
            <h3>Integration with WIA-OMNI-API</h3>
            <p>
                WIA-OMNI-API provides a universal API layer. Consent verification is embedded into API
                access control:
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">GET /api/omni/user/789012/profile
Authorization: Bearer {token}
X-WIA-Consent-Check: required

Response Headers:
X-WIA-Consent-Status: verified
X-WIA-Consent-Id: consent-550e8400...
X-WIA-Purposes: profile-access,analytics

Response Body:
{
  "userId": "user-789012",
  "profile": { ... },
  "consentCompliance": {
    "verified": true,
    "purposes": ["profile-access", "analytics"]
  }
}</div>
            <h3>Integration with WIA-SOCIAL</h3>
            <p>
                WIA-SOCIAL governs social platform interactions. Consent flows across social connections:
