            <h2>Regulatory Compliance Integration</h2>
            <h3>GDPR Compliance Mapping</h3>
            <p>WIA-CORE-002 fields map directly to GDPR requirements:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Article 7:</strong> Conditions for consent вҶ’ purposes[].granted, auditTrail</li>
                <li><strong>Article 13:</strong> Information to be provided вҶ’ metadata.privacyPolicyUrl</li>
                <li><strong>Article 15:</strong> Right of access вҶ’ API GET /consents/{id}</li>
                <li><strong>Article 17:</strong> Right to erasure вҶ’ API DELETE /consents/{id}</li>
                <li><strong>Article 20:</strong> Right to data portability вҶ’ API GET /users/{id}/consents/export</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>CCPA Compliance Mapping</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Right to Opt-Out:</strong> purposes[].granted = false</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Know:</strong> API GET /users/{id}/consents</li>
                <li><strong>Right to Delete:</strong> API DELETE /users/{id}/consents</li>
                <li><strong>Do Not Sell:</strong> purposes where category includes "sale" or "sharing"</li>
            </ul>
            <h2>Migration Pathways</h2>
            <h3>From Legacy Systems</h3>
            <p>Migrating from legacy consent management systems to WIA-CORE-002:</p>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Data Mapping:</strong> Map legacy fields to WIA-CORE-002 schema</li>
                <li><strong>Gap Analysis:</strong> Identify missing required fields</li>
                <li><strong>Backfill Strategy:</strong> Plan for filling gaps (e.g., re-consent campaigns)</li>
                <li><strong>Parallel Running:</strong> Run legacy and new systems in parallel</li>
                <li><strong>Gradual Migration:</strong> Migrate users in batches</li>
                <li><strong>Validation:</strong> Verify data integrity post-migration</li>
                <li><strong>Cutover:</strong> Switch primary system to WIA-CORE-002</li>
                <li><strong>Legacy Decommission:</strong> Archive legacy system after validation period</li>
            </ol>
